quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  5,24,"They said, \"O Moses! We shall never enter it so long as they are therein; so, go you and your Lord and fight you two; we will sit down here"
  5,25,"Said he, \"My Lord, verily, I can control only myself and my brother; therefore, part (distinguish) us from this rebellious people"
  5,26,"He (the Lord) said, \"Then, verily, this land is forbidden them for forty years; in bewilderment shall they wander about in the earth; so grieve not yourself for these sinful people"
  5,27,"Recite to them the true tale of the two sons of Adam; truly when they offered an offering and it was accepted from one of them, and not from the other. Said the latter, \"I will surely kill you.\" Said the former, \"Surely, Allah only accepts"
  5,28,"If you do stretch forth your hand to kill me, I will not stretch forth mine to kill you; for, verily, I fear Allah the Lord of the Worlds"
  5,29,"Verily, I would rather that you draw upon yourself my sin and yours, and become of the fellows of the Fire, for that is the reward of the evil-doer (or unjust)"
  5,30,"But the other´s soul compelled him to slay his brother, and so he slew him, and became one of the losers"
  5,31,"Then Allah sent a crow to scratch in the earth and show him how he might hide his brother´s naked corpse. He said, \"Alas, for me! Am I too helpless to become like this crow and hide my brother´s naked corpse?\" and in the morning he w"